s:716:"<p>Toggle buttons that determine if a specific row can be seen or hidden at various screen widths, or whether it should be displayed in a stacked layout (all positions are 100% width) or whether the layout widths should override the grid collapse setting.</p>
<p><img style="" alt="Responsive" src="/docs/buildr-documentation/user/pages/06.row-settings/02.responsive/responsive.png" /></p>
<h2>Screenwidths</h2>
<p>The framework is capable of targeting 5 different breakpoints.</p>
<ul>
<li>desktop</li>
<li>tablet</li>
<li>phone</li>
<li>nav collapse</li>
<li>grid collapse</li>
</ul>
<p>The specific px values for these breakpoints are set in the layout &gt; breakpoint panel of the general setting side panel.</p>";